rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:22:"Daniel Alves de Jesus.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1949:"<p>If you have migrated your WordPress website, switched to a new domain or created a local copy for testing, chances are you will need to update links to point to your new location. You can easily change this with the <a title="open Plugin website in a new window" href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/search-and-replace/" target="_blank">Search &amp; Replace</a> plugin.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to the admin area of your WordPress installation by entering the respective URL in your browser.</li>\n<li>Install the <strong>Search &amp; Replace</strong> plugin.</li>\n<li>Under the name of the plugin you have just installed, click <strong>Settings</strong>.</li>\n<li>Enter the URL of your &#8220;previous WordPress installation&#8221; in the <strong>Search for</strong> field.</li>\n<li>Activate the <strong>All &#8211; search and replace!</strong> option.</li>\n<li>Enter the URL of your new WordPress installation in the <strong>Replace with</strong> field.<br />\nFor a local copy it could look something like this: http://localhost/<strong>wp-testenvironment/</strong></li>\n<li>Click <strong>Go</strong>.<br />\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1397" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/url-ersetzen-01_en.png" alt="Replacing URL" width="918" height="476" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/url-ersetzen-01_en.png 918w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/url-ersetzen-01_en-300x155.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 918px) 100vw, 918px" /><br />\nThe changes are being applied.</li>\n<li>Click <strong>Settings &gt; Permalinks</strong>.</li>\n<li>Select <strong>Post name</strong> and click <strong>Save Changes</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/fixing-broken-links-wordpress/">Fixing Broken Links of a WordPress Installation</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:63:"https://community.1and1.com/fixing-broken-links-wordpress/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:4:"href";s:52:"https://community.1and1.com/category/wordpress/feed/";s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"hourly";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:15:"updateFrequency";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:"type";i:128;s:7:"headers";O:42:"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary":1:{s:7:"\0*\0data";a:12:{s:4:"date";s:29:"Wed, 20 Dec 2017 12:16:51 GMT";s:6:"server";s:6:"Apache";s:13:"last-modified";s:29:"Fri, 08 Dec 2017 10:31:03 GMT";s:4:"etag";s:34:""fb5b35b36375d90f90198885639a0ba5"";s:12:"x-robots-t